<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BF9D3FA2DFA0A" box="[136,1451,1461,1483]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
4. Stipular glands absent, sometimes present only in some parts, then barely conspicuous.................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D1FB61DFA83F9D3FA2DFA0A" authorityName="A. Heller" authorityYear="1898" box="[1344,1451,1461,1483]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Linum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australe">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFA83F9D3FA2DFA0A" bold="true" box="[1344,1451,1461,1483]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">L. australe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BF9B4FA2CFA26" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1450,1489,1512]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BF9B4FA2CFA26" box="[136,1450,1489,1512]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
- Stipular glands present throughout the plant, very conspicuous .......................................................... 
