<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFB4FF9B4FA2CFA26" bold="true" box="[1164,1450,1489,1511]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFB4FF9B4FB71FA26" bold="true" box="[1164,1271,1489,1511]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">L. australe</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFAEAF9B7FA2CFA26" bold="true" box="[1321,1450,1489,1511]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">glandulosum</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="805D2E250D1FB61DFF4BF988FA2DF9E0" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BF988FA2DF9C4" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1451,1518,1541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BF988FA2DF9C4" box="[136,1451,1518,1541]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">5. Stems pilose locally or throughout .....................................................................................................................................................6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BFA6AFA2DF9E0" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1451,1547,1569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BFA6AFA2DF9E0" box="[136,1451,1547,1569]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">-. Stems glabrous throughout .................................................................................................................................................................7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="805D2E250D1FB61DFF4BFA4EFA2CF99A" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BFA4EFA2CF9FF" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1450,1576,1598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BFA4EFA2CF9FF" box="[136,1450,1576,1598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
6. Plant hirsutulose at the base; sepals glabrous; fruit with translucent thin pericarp............................... 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D1FB61DFB50FA4FFA2CF9FF" authorityName="C. M. Rogers" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Shinners" box="[1171,1450,1576,1598]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Linum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="berlandieri" variety="filifolium">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFB50FA4FFA2CF9FF" bold="true" box="[1171,1450,1576,1598]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFB50FA4FFA9DF9FF" bold="true" box="[1171,1307,1576,1598]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">L. berlandieri</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFA8EFA4EFA2CF9FF" bold="true" box="[1357,1450,1576,1598]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">filifolium</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BFA23FA2CF99A" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1450,1605,1627]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BFA23FA2CF99A" box="[136,1450,1605,1627]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
- Plant densely gray-puberulent to the inflorescence; sepals pubescent; fruit with thick opaque pericarp ..................... 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D1FB61DFAE0FA23FA2CF99A" authorityName="A. Heller" authorityYear="1896" box="[1315,1450,1605,1627]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Linum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="puberulum">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFAE0FA23FA2CF99A" bold="true" box="[1315,1450,1605,1627]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">L. puberulum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="805D2E250D1FB61DFF4BFA04FA2CF955" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BFA04FA2CF9B6" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1450,1633,1656]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BFA04FA2CF9B6" box="[136,1450,1633,1656]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
7. Basal leaves alternate; sepals deciduous, 3-nerved; anthers brick-red........................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D1FB61DFAE4FA04FA2CF9B6" authorityName="H. J. P. Winkler" authorityYear="1931" baseAuthorityName="Small" box="[1319,1450,1633,1655]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Linum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="elongatum">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFAE4FA04FA2CF9B6" bold="true" box="[1319,1450,1633,1655]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">L. elongatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3B1636800D1FB61DFF4BFA19FA2CF955" blockId="5.[136,1451,1288,2088]" box="[136,1450,1662,1685]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
<keyLead id="805895B50D1FB61DFF4BFA19FA2CF955" box="[136,1450,1662,1685]" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">
-. Basal leaves opposite; sepals persistent, 1-nerved; anthers brown ..................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="FCA94D030D1FB61DFA84FA19FA2CF955" authorityName="Wooton" authorityYear="1898" box="[1351,1450,1662,1684]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Linaceae" genus="Linum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="146" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vernale">
<emphasis id="09DDEA920D1FB61DFA84FA19FA2CF955" bold="true" box="[1351,1450,1662,1684]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="146">L. vernale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
